## Schema

### Required

- `name` (String) Channel name. Must be unique within the org.

### Optional (Phase 2 supported)

- `slack_configs` (Attributes List) One or more Slack receivers. (see below for nested schema)

### Optional (Phase 2 rejected — schema only)

- `discord_configs`, `email_configs`, `incidentio_configs`, `jira_configs`, `mattermost_configs`, `msteams_configs`, `opsgenie_configs`, `pagerduty_configs`, `pushover_configs`, `rocketchat_configs`, `sns_configs`, `telegram_configs`, `victorops_configs`, `webex_configs`, `webhook_configs`, `wechat_configs` (Attributes List). Setting any of these fails apply.

### Read-Only

- `id` (String) Autogenerated unique ID.
- `org_id` (String) ID of the org the channel belongs to.
- `type` (String) Server-derived channel type discriminator (e.g., `slack`).

### Nested Schema for `slack_configs`

The fields below mirror the upstream Prometheus alertmanager Slack receiver. All are optional.

Common:

- `api_url` (String) Slack incoming-webhook URL. Mutually-set with `api_url_file`.
- `api_url_file` (String) Path to a file containing the webhook URL.
- `channel` (String) Slack channel (e.g., `#alerts`).
- `username` (String) Override sender username.
- `send_resolved` (Boolean) Send a follow-up message when alerts resolve.

Message body:

- `title` (String), `title_link` (String), `text` (String), `pretext` (String), `fallback` (String), `footer` (String), `color` (String), `message_text` (String).
- `icon_emoji` (String), `icon_url` (String), `image_url` (String), `thumb_url` (String).
- `mrkdwn_in` (List of String) Fields where Slack mrkdwn is enabled.
- `link_names` (Boolean), `short_fields` (Boolean).

Interactive:

- `actions` (Attributes List) Slack action buttons. Each item has `name`, `type`, `text`, `style`, `url`, `value`, and optional `confirm` (with `dismiss_text`, `ok_text`, `text`, `title`).
- `fields` (Attributes List) Slack message fields. Each item has `title`, `value`, `short`.
- `callback_id` (String) Slack callback ID for action buttons.

Slack app auth (alternative to webhooks):

- `app_token` (String), `app_token_file` (String), `app_url` (String).

Transport:

- `http_config` (Attributes) HTTP client config: TLS, proxy, basic auth, OAuth2, bearer token. See alertmanager docs for the full shape.
- `timeout` (Number) Request timeout (server-side units).
